Assumption category: For R1 article, the code available is assumed to be the same as was used in the original experiments
For R1 article, the parameter values in available code is assumed to be the same as was used in the original experiments
For R1 article, trained weights or parameters shared with code are assumed to be the same as was used in the original experiments
For R1 article, a minor change in code to facilitate running on our hardware is assumed to be inconsequential to the end result
An assumption is made about how to interpret a term or concept which is ambigous
An assumption is made about how to treat an aspect of the method which is not well described

Assumptions are made in the implementation of the method in the presence of unclear description

An assumption is made about how to extract a subset from a data set
